<p-lede
  ><a href="https://muralartsinstitute.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
    >Mural Arts Institute (MAI)</a
  >
  is dedicated to sharing knowledge, ideas, and experiences that have shaped our
  approach to community-centered artmaking.</p-lede
>
<p
  >Our goal is to help foster spaces and co-learning experiences that advance
  artists in their professional practices and strengthen our arts ecosystem
  through free training, events, and more! This includes our
  <a
    href="https://muralartsinstitute.com/artist-directory/"
    target="_blank"
    rel="noopener"
    >Artist Directory</a
  >
  with a growing list of Philadelphia public art practitioners.</p
>
<p
  >Mural Arts Institute would like to recognize
  <a
    href="https://muralarts.org/artists/david-mcshane/"
    target="_blank"
    rel="noopener"
    >David McShane</a
  >
  for his 30 years of commitment to public artmaking and his mentorship role
  with Mural Arts, providing leadership in the Muralist Training Program for
  over two decades and providing instruction to hundreds of artists, interns,
  apprentices, consulting clients, and program participants during this time.
  Learn more about Davidâ€™ s work and contributions in this
  <a
    href="https://muralarts.org/stories/a-conversation-with-dave-mcshane-reflecting-on-30-years/"
    target="_blank"
    rel="noopener"
    >blog</a
  >.</p
>
